module: a2-09
level: A2
sequence: 9
slug: all-cases-practice
version: '2.0'
title: All Cases Practice
subtitle: Consolidating the Case System
content_outline:
- section: Introduction / Вступ
  points:
  - 'Importance of the 7-case system — cultural hook: Ukrainian has 7 cases (unlike
    English''s few) which creates its famous melody and emotional nuance (Vocative);
    often ranked 2nd most melodic language after Italian'
  - Quick reference table — establish 'Court Translator' persona for precision in
    endings, encouraging 'legal' accuracy
- section: Presentation / Презентація
  points:
  - Case-by-case review (Nom to Voc) — aligns with State Standard §4.2.2 (all 7 cases,
    singular/plural)
  - 'Gender forms summary — learner error: confusing Genitive and Accusative for animate
    masculine nouns (''Я бачу друга'', not ''Я бачу друг'')'
  - 'Strategic question-based approach — focus on question words as triggers: хто/що,
    кого/чого, кому/чому, ким/чим, на кому/на чому'
- section: Practice / Практика
  points:
  - 'Mixed case identification — learner error: using Locative without a preposition
    (''Я працюю в лікарні'', not ''Я працюю лікарні'')'
  - 'Paradigms for key nouns (друг, книга) — learner error: using Nominative for age
    instead of Dative (''Мені 20 років'', not ''Я 20 років'')'
- section: Dialogues / Діалоги
  points:
  - 'Real-world application of mixed cases — focus on precision and correctness in
    everyday scenarios; context: legal/official scenarios to fit Court Translator
    persona'
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - хто (who) — хто це? (High freq)
  - що (what) — що це? (High freq)
  - кого (whom - acc/gen) — нема кого (High freq)
  - чого (of what) — нема чого (High freq)
  - кому (to whom) — дати комусь (High freq)
  - чому (to what / why) — чому ти тут? (High freq)
  - ким (by whom) — бути кимсь (High freq)
  - чим (by what) — задоволений чимсь (High freq)
  - відмінок (case) — відмінювати за відмінками (Academic)
  - називний (nominative) — суб'єкт (State Standard)
  - родовий (genitive) — заперечення, кількість (State Standard)
  - давальний (dative) — адресат (State Standard)
  - знахідний (accusative) — прямий об'єкт (State Standard)
  - орудний (instrumental) — знаряддя, супровід (State Standard)
  - місцевий (locative) — місце, на кому / на чому (State Standard)
  recommended:
  - кличний (vocative) — звертання (State Standard)
  - однина (singular)
  - множина (plural)
  - закінчення (ending)
  - відмінювати (to decline)
activity_hints:
- type: fill-in
  focus: Choose correct case for context
  items: 15+
- type: fill-in
  focus: Decline nouns through all 7 cases
  items: 8+
- type: quiz
  focus: Identify case by ending
  items: 15+
- type: match-up
  focus: Case + question word + function
  items: 10+
- type: fill-in
  focus: Error correction - fix wrong cases
  items: 10+
- type: quiz
  focus: Mixed case selection in paragraphs
  items: 10+
focus: grammar
pedagogy: PPP
prerequisites:
- a2-01 through a2-08 (all case modules)
- A1 case basics (Nom, Acc, Gen, Loc)
connects_to:
- a2-10 (Post Office & Bank - application)
- a2-11 (Checkpoint - Cases)
- All subsequent A2 modules
objectives:
- Learner can identify which case is required in a given context
- Learner can form correct endings for all 7 cases
- Learner can switch between cases fluently in conversation
- Learner can correct common case errors
grammar:
- all 7 cases review
- case selection logic
- common prepositions
- case endings
module_type: grammar
sources:
- name: Ukrainian State Standard 2024 - Case System
  url: https://mon.gov.ua/
  type: reference
  notes: Complete 7-case paradigm requirements for A2
- name: Ukrainian Case System Reference
  url: https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Відмінок
  type: reference
  notes: Complete declension tables
immersion: 50-60% Ukrainian
phase: A2.1
persona:
  voice: Encouraging Cultural Guide
  role: Court Translator
word_target: 3000
